<h3>Malise</h3>
<p>Have you been frustrated by spell resists?&nbsp; At 24, magicians can cast
Malise.&nbsp; The target's fire, cold, magic and poison resists all drop when
this spell lands.&nbsp; The spell itself is resisted frequently, however.&nbsp;
Shaman also get this spell at an earlier level.&nbsp; If you're grouped with a
shaman let him or her know if you will Malise.&nbsp; Casting it twice is just
wasting mana.</p>

<p>Since your pet is lower than the mobs you may be fighting, its spells are
often resisted.&nbsp; Malise is an excellent way to make sure that your pet's
spells stick.</p>

<p>Malise does not generate a lot of hate (aggro).&nbsp; However, if you cast 
this right away, you may become the mob's primary target.  Let a tank get in a
couple of rounds before you cast.</p>

<h3>Staff of Runes</h3>
<p>This staff has a single charge of Cancel Magic.&nbsp; Although this may not
seem all that useful at first, it is a great backup.&nbsp; Suppose you are out
of mana and have a magic-based DOT on you.&nbsp; If you had a staff already
summoned, you could cancel the DOT.&nbsp; You can give this staff to non-magic
users and they too can cancel magic.&nbsp; This spell is actually useful all the
way to 60.&nbsp; It has uses in pvp as well.</p>

<h3>New Pet Skill</h3>
<p>Your pet may now dual wield.&nbsp; Give the pet 2 1-handed weapons and it will use them both</p>

<p><i>Historical Note: There is a lot of out of date information on pets and
weapons.&nbsp; A long time ago, the stats on a weapon greatly affected the
damage output of the pet.&nbsp; This is no longer the case.&nbsp; In short, pet
attacks were broken.&nbsp; It took a year to convince Verant of the problem
(pets were not both double attacking and dual wielding).&nbsp; Once this problem
was fixed, Verant decided that pets were overpowered.&nbsp; Pet melee rules were changed.&nbsp; Although pets now 
properly dual-wield and double attack (based on level), weapon delay is ignored by the pet.&nbsp; Pets attack at the same speed,
regardless of the weapon speed.&nbsp; All four pets attack at the same
speed.&nbsp; (Fire used to attack very quickly).</i></p>

